It is that speck of dust.

01:25.085 --> 01:27.254
Where are all these planets hiding?

01:27.337 --> 01:31.550
When you look at the night sky,
all you see is space and stars.

01:31.633 --> 01:36.096
True, but each of those stars is
a sun that might have its own planets.

01:36.763 --> 01:37.973
<i>Exactly!</i>

01:40.559 --> 01:42.102
<i>Sorry about that.</i>

01:42.186 --> 01:45.022
<i>I've been working
on my dramatic entrances.</i>

01:45.856 --> 01:46.982
<i>But Marcie is right.</i>

01:47.065 --> 01:48.817
<i>Every star is a sun,</i>

01:48.901 --> 01:53.030
<i>and the planets orbiting
those distant suns are called exoplanets,</i>

01:53.113 --> 01:55.574
<i>or planets outside of our solar system.</i>

01:56.158 --> 01:58.660
<i>NASA has been looking for them for years.</i>

